# One canonical byte stream on every platform. CI (Linux) has always scanned the
# LF bytes stored in the index; core.autocrlf=true checkouts on Windows scanned
# CRLF for some files and LF for others (the working tree was mixed). YARA
# verdicts must not depend on which OS ran the harness, so every text file is
# LF in the index AND in the working tree. eol=lf overrides core.autocrlf.
#
# If a sample must one day carry CRLF bytes on purpose (a CRLF-sensitive rule),
# pin that file here with `-text` instead of letting the checkout platform decide.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never eol-normalize, never diff as text.
*.png binary
